<br>
At lvl 61, lvl 48 mobs are blue.<br>
<br>
At lvl 62, lvl 50 or 51 mobs are blue (epic pet and half of PoD are light blue).<br>
<br>
For those of you who are 65, does this progression continue?  If so, I guess my solo career is over.  I am pretty much forced to hydra at 62 as it is.  It is vaguely disheartening, since I - and several others I know - selected the magician class specifically for our ability to solo.<br>
<br>
The high-damage, low hit point mobs of PoP really cater to those who can can control their environment.  It is a huge solo *boost* to those who can either root-dot or quad-kite.  I am forced to use the epic (GVocs last about 8-10 seconds and do approximately 3-5% damage to a mob in PoN when buffed), and thus I must either rely on regeneration or heals to prepare my pet for another pull, incurring ludicrous downtime.  Alternatively, I can reclaim him, mana boost, and summon/buff another epic.  This limits me to one pull per 5 minutes; i.e., hardly satisfactory.<br>
<br>
Does the level gap trend continue?  <br>
<br>
If so, I guess my number 1 priority becomes getting my hands on a 61+ pet (chain-casting) or getting Suspend II (mana ramping while retaining active pet).  Given the number of parchments I have seen drop, Suspend II is looking good.<br>
<br>
